    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Feb 13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1882</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I must write one line to thank you &amp; M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Tait for your very kind note on my birthday.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I feel a very old man, &amp; my course is nearly run.—</p>
<p>I remain— | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The note from Lawson and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7486.xml">Sybil Anne Tait</ref> has not been found. CD’s birthday was 12 February; he was 73.</note>    
        </div>
    
